President Trump and his administration met with survivors of the recent school shooting in Parkland, Florida, to discuss potential solutions to prevent future incidents. The President expressed his condolences and assured the attendees that the administration is committed to finding a solution. Some of the ideas discussed during the meeting included strengthening background checks, focusing on mental health issues, arming teachers or other school staff members, and improving school security measures. The President emphasized the need for immediate action and promised to work towards implementing the strongest and most effective ideas.